<inglise> COUNCIL REGULATION (ECSC, EEC, EURATOM) No 2764/79 of 6 December 1979 amending Regulation (ECSC, EEC, Euratom) No 300/76 determining the categories of officials entitled to allowances for shiftwork, and the rates and conditions thereof </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 2764/79, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 300/76, millega m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks ametnike kategooriad, kellel on &otilde;igus saada h&uuml;vitist vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml; eest, ning selle h&uuml;vitise m&auml;&auml;rad ja maksmise tingimused 6. detsember 1979 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC, Euratom, ECSC) No 259/68 laying down the Staff Regulations of officials and conditions of employment of other servants of the European Communities (1), as last amended by Regulation (Euratom, ECSC, EEC) No 3085/78 (2), and in particular the second paragraph of Article 56a of the Staff Regulations, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;, Euratom, EST&Uuml;) nr 259/68 (milles s&auml;testatakse Euroopa &uuml;henduste ametnike personalieeskirjad ja &uuml;henduste muude teenistujate teenistustingimused), (1) viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (Euratom, EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;) nr 3085/78, (2) eriti personalieeskirjade artikli 56a teist l&otilde;iku, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission, submitted after consulting the Staff Regulations Committee, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse ettepanekut, mille komisjon esitas p&auml;rast n&otilde;upidamist personalieeskirjade komiteega ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas it is for the Council, acting on a proposal from the Commission submitted after consulting the Staff Regulations Committee, to determine the categories of officials entitled to allowances for shiftwork, and the rates and conditions thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> n&otilde;ukogu &uuml;lesanne on komisjoni ettepaneku p&otilde;hjal, mille viimane esitab p&auml;rast n&otilde;upidamist personalieeskirjade komiteega, m&auml;&auml;rata kindlaks ametnike kategooriad, kellel on &otilde;igus saada h&uuml;vitist vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml; eest, ning selle h&uuml;vitise m&auml;&auml;rad ja maksmise tingimused, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas staff employed in certain telex services do shiftwork within the meaning of Article 56a of the Staff Regulations; whereas Regulation (ECSC, EEC, Euratom) No 300/76 (3) should be correspondingly amended, </inglise>
<eesti> teatavate teleksiteenuseid osutavate asutuste t&ouml;&ouml;tajad teevad vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml;d personalieeskirjade artikli 56a t&auml;henduses; m&auml;&auml;ruses (EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 300/76 (3) tuleks teha vastavad muudatused, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> In Article 1 (1) of Regulation (ECSC, EEC, Euratom) No 300/76 the text of the part of the first subparagraph preceding the indents shall be replaced by the following: </inglise>
<eesti> M&auml;&auml;ruse (EST&Uuml;, EM&Uuml;, Euratom) nr 300/76 artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 1 asendatakse esimese l&otilde;igu taanetele eelnev tekst j&auml;rgmisega: </eesti>
<inglise> "1. </inglise>
<eesti> "1. </eesti>
<inglise> An official paid from research and investment appropriations and employed in an establishment of the Joint Research Centre or in indirect action, or paid from operating appropriations and employed in a computer centre, a security department or a telex service, who is engaged in shiftwork within the meaning of Article 56a of the Staff Regulations, shall be entitled to an allowance of:" </inglise>
<eesti> Personalieeskirjade artikli 56a t&auml;henduses vahetustega t&ouml;&ouml;taval ametnikul, kellele makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;tasu teadusuuringute ja investeeringute eelarvest ja kes t&ouml;&ouml;tab Teadusuuringute &Uuml;hiskeskuse asutuses v&otilde;i on h&otilde;lmatud kaudse tegevuse projektiga v&otilde;i kellele makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;tasu tegevuseelarvest ja kes t&ouml;&ouml;tab m&otilde;nes andmet&ouml;&ouml;tluskeskuses, turvaosakonnas v&otilde;i teleksiteenuseid osutavas asutuses, on &otilde;igus saada h&uuml;vitist:" </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas avaldamisele j&auml;rgneval p&auml;eval. </eesti>
<inglise> It shall apply from 1 January 1980. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolevat m&auml;&auml;rust kohaldatakse alates 1. jaanuarist 1980. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 6 December 1979. </inglise>
